{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ac07af28-1023-40cb-a866-041b7debb483","content":"No files exist in the workspace — this is a guidance question. Here's exactly what to do:\n\n## 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the CLR namespace and set `x:DataType` on the `ContentPage`:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat single `x:DataType` attribute is the switch. Every `{Binding}` inside that element is now **compiled** — the XAML compiler resolves property names against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n## 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already produce **build errors** for typos or type mismatches. To ensure nothing slips through:\n\n1. **Enable warnings-as-errors** for binding diagnostics in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TreatWarningsAsErrors>true</TreatWarningsAsErrors>\n     <!-- or selectively: -->\n     <WarningsAsErrors>XC0045;XC0022</WarningsAsErrors>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Avoid `x:DataType` escapes** — if any sub-element sets `x:DataType=\"x:Null\"`, that subtree reverts to reflection-based bindings and skips compile-time checks.\n\n3. **Build regularly** (`dotnet build`) — misspelled properties like `{Binding Themee}` will now fail the build with an error pointing to the exact line.\n\n## Key rules\n\n| Do | Don't |\n|---|---|\n| Set `x:DataType` on root or nearest container | Leave it off (falls back to runtime reflection) |\n| Use strongly-typed paths: `{Binding FontSize}` | Use string indexers or untyped casts |\n| Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for collections | Assume parent `x:DataType` flows into templates |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"46cc1fc4-c14e-4882-bfa1-1598b938a068","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty. The user is asking a conceptual question about converting a MAUI page to compiled bindings. I'll provide the answer directly since there are no files to modify.","outputTokens":668,"requestId":"0452:30C599:A89190:C1238A:6A027970"},"id":"d6fe0e01-bee9-4eb0-8eb9-0a13f372b64e","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:51:12.131Z","parentId":"56c75763-7bb4-4e15-b0b5-8882bad6503c"}
